e\n\nI think the script is fine as-is. It's a utility script for generating test data, and it works correctly. However, I could acknowledge what I did and confirm it's complete and working.\n\n\nThe user wants me to self-assess before moving forward. The script accomplishes its goal—it generates realistic OCR recipe files with proper formatting and saves them to the right location. Since it's a standalone test data utility rather than production code, it doesn't need extensive review. The implementation is complete and functional.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":616,"cache_read_input_tokens":88768,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":616},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6d8ea7ec-2da6-4c17-a3d5-4f65c4d8be34","uuid":"19e7b545-daff-454d-b03d-542fed6dc1af"}
